---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Trust & safety" description="How ServicesInMyCity earns your trust: earned recommendations, no fake reviews, consent-first, and clear limits.">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Trust &amp; safety</h1>
      <p class="lede">Your trust is worth more to us than revenue. Here's how we protect it.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container" style="padding:40px 20px 64px">
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card"><h3>Earned, never purchased</h3><p>Recommendations are earned. No business can buy its way to the top here.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>No fake anything</h3><p>We never fabricate reviews, ratings, or contractor counts. Honest empty states over fake numbers.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Rocco equips, never diagnoses</h3><p>Rocco gives you understanding and questions &mdash; not a diagnosis. He never replaces a licensed pro.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Consent is a gate</h3><p>We don't collect more than we need. Sharing anything is optional and gated by your consent.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>No accounts in Phase 1</h3><p>No email, no password, no profile. Just help.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Honest local data</h3><p>Nearby businesses come from Google and are shown as exactly that &mdash; not Rocco's ranked picks.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="disclaimer" style="margin-top:24px">
      See also: <a href="/data">how your data works</a>, <a href="/legal/disclaimers">disclaimers</a>, and <a href="/legal/privacy">privacy</a>.
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
